Blackguard of the 57th pilfer<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/11/02 11:58:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly tanks</span><hr size=1> Being on a red server isn't much of an excuse to use obvious bugs like ghosting.<br>
<br>
How far do you want to go with that logic? How about hacks? What about showeq?  How about training to soften them up?  Waiting for a group to pull mobs than raining them?  How about using a pet to target a melee and nuking them through walls?<br>
<br>
The water deal really isn't a bug its a design issue that has nothing to do with pvp.  The deal is swimming mobs can't leave the water so if you could cast through the water you could easily exp by nuking swimming mobs from the shore.  I agree with the line of sight issue being in the water removes los. Besides which this can benifit or harm every class depending on if you know how to use it.  A nuker can nail another caster then dodge the other parties nuke.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/12/02 12:35:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 60 wiz vrs level 60 Rogue</span><hr size=1> In reply to...<br>
<br>
&quot;Slightly OT, but I find it amusing that melees can &quot;take&quot; casters at all. One of the things I've always enjoyed about fantasy novels is the mystique and power of elite spellcasters (the Dragonlance triolgy comes to mind). Wizards in particular have a long and difficult road to 60; why should some random assassin be able to get anywhere NEAR a 60 wizard? &quot;<br>
<br>
Several points...<br>
<br>
I don't think wizards have it any harder than anyone else getting to 60 from scatch.  Hell if a rogue and a wizard lvl in the same group of friends they will reach 60 the same day.<br>
<br>
A lvl 60 EQ rogue isn't &quot;some random assassin&quot; he's supposed to be I think a brutal fighter in close quarters and a master of all his arts.   Silent and deadly.  Also looking at fantasy fiction the most powerful magicians are still vulnerable to a knife in the back (those that aren't undead, immortal or demi gods).  In fact more so because their dedication to the mastery of their art leaves them no time for physical training and heavy armor would be too encumbering.<br>
<br>
How much fun would that realisticly be for the rogue? Giving one class a huge advantage such that they are invincible or nearly so in every situation (you allready are outdoors if your smart) while possessing a strong offense as well would just create disatisfaction and frustration.  It suits a cleric well to be nearly unkillable solo because this defensive strength is matched by offensive weakness.  For a rogue to be a joke defensively AND offensively would be pathetic and very poor design and trust me rogues defense IS a joke.  Our only real defense is a strong offense.  It's how its supposed to be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showMessageRange?topicID=19.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showMessageRange?topicID=19.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=19.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=19.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=44><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.threadControl?topicID=19.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br>